  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education for crisis affected people on the move</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Migration and mobility are not new, but their scale is unprecedented. Ensuring the provision of quality education for refugees, migrants and internally displaced persons is a growing issue, which needs to be addressed from a long-term perspective. To this end, UNESCO will expand its work to support Member States, both countries of origin and host countries, to build responsive and resilient education systems, and provide equitable quality education and access to lifelong learning opportunities. Special emphasis will be placed on technical and vocational education and training (TVET) and the recognition of skills and higher education qualifications for these groups.</narrative>
  </description>
